Subject: [PATCH 0/8] arm64: allwinner: Add initial A733 and Cubie A7S support

Draft only. Do not send this series until the open items below are resolved.

This series adds initial mainline support for the Allwinner A733 SoC and the
Radxa Cubie A7S board. The initial board DTS enables only UART0 and MMC0.
Ethernet is intentionally left out of scope.

This draft does not include Ethernet, VPU/Cedrus, or any deferred parent IRQ
registration workaround. Those areas need separate subsystem-specific series
and evidence before they can be proposed.

Known in-flight work:

- Junhui Liu posted an RFC for A733 CCU and PRCM support:
  https://lore.kernel.org/r/20260310-a733-clk-v1-0-36b4e9b24457@pigmoral.tech
- Andre Przywara posted an RFC for A733 pinctrl support:
  https://lore.kernel.org/r/20250821004232.8134-1-andre.przywara@arm.com

Before this can be sent, the CCU and pinctrl patches must either be rebased on
top of the relevant in-flight work, coordinated with the authors, or explained
clearly as a deliberate divergence.

Validation completed locally:

- git am of the exported patches onto the recorded base: pass
- git diff --check: pass
- scripts/checkpatch.pl --strict on patches 1-8: pass except MAINTAINERS
  new-file questions
- make dt_binding_check for touched schemas: pass
- make ARCH=arm64 CHECK_DTBS=y dtbs_check for the Cubie A7S DTB with
  colon-separated DT_SCHEMA_FILES: pass
- W=1 object build for the new CCU and pinctrl drivers: pass

Open items before submission:

- record a hardware boot log from a Cubie A7S using this exact kernel and DTB
- record per-patch bisectability checks for the exported series
- verify whether MAINTAINERS needs explicit sun60i patterns or file entries
- decide how this series relates to the in-flight CCU and pinctrl RFCs
- regenerate this cover letter without the draft/no-send language

